One down, seven to go! Next up is the Antares League gym in Centauri City . Your route to get there first goes east through Deimos Forest . The forest's entrance is just north of the eastern part of Sol City.
What is Team Nova doing in the forest? Surely it can't be good. Whatever it is, they seem pretty focused, because they will ignore you as long as you let them.

What's up with all the Arakids? Well, we can worry about that later. They're clearly up to something! Disrupt their plans as much as you like.
Deimos Forest is pretty big. If you need to heal, then the researcher in the small cave can help you out.
When you reach the end of the forest, you'll find a few Team Nova recruits who have already completed whatever mission they've been on. Eavesdrop for a while. Enter Mimas who happens to be strolling by.
Needless to say, this doesn't end well; intervene and help Mimas out.

Heroics done, leave the forest and rest for a while in Ligeia Village . It's a quiet place with not much to do, but take care to get the fishing rod before leaving!
The rest of the road to Centauri City should be pretty uneventful, if long. Head up through Cepheus Pass and eventually you'll wind your way over to Centauri City .
Isn't that the raving man from the underground cave? What the heck is he doing here? Whatever it is, he doesn't want you to know - he'll disappear as soon as he notices you.
Poke around enough and you'll eventually find your way over to the dock.
Something interesting is happening. It's about to get a little more interesting.
